        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 11 at 5:47PM CDT until August 11 at 6:45PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
East central Oldham County in the Panhandle of Texas...
West central Potter County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 645 PM CDT.

* At 547 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles southwest
of Valley De Oro, or 14 miles northeast of Vega, and is nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Hail damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Valley De Oro.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
